{"name": "pnoise", "metadata": {"name": "pnoise", "version": "0.2.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Lesser General Public License v2 or later (LGPLv2+)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Multimedia :: Graphics", "Typing :: Typed"], "home_page": "https://github.com/plottertools/pnoise", "license": "LGPL 2.1", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy"], "summary": "Vectorized port of Processing noise() function", "upload_time": 1650376954}, "documentation": ["# *pnoise*\n\n*pnoise* is a pure-Python, Numpy-based, vectorized port of Processing's `noise()` function. The `p` in *pnoise* stands for Processing, Perlin, Python, \"port\", and probably other things I haven't though of yet.\n\n## Why?\n\nI wrote this port before switching to [vnoise](https://github.com/plottertools/vnoise) and, although I'm no longer using it, I figured I would keep it around. \n\n## How does it compare to *vnoise*?\n\n| | *pnoise* | *vnoise* |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Algorithm | \"classic Perlin noise of 1983\" | \"Perlin improved noise\" |\n| License | LGPL v2.1 | MIT |\n| Scalar API | \u2705 | \u2705 |\n| Vectorized API | \u2705 | \u2705 |\n| 3D function | \u2705 | \u2705 |\n| 2D function | \u274c (can be derived from 3D but slower) | \u2705 |\n| 1D function | \u274c (can be derived from 3D but slower) | \u2705 |\n\nSee a performance comparison [here](https://github.com/plottertools/vnoise/tree/main/benchmarks).\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install pnoise\n```\n\n## License\n\nLGPL 2.1, see [LICENSE](LICENSE) file.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pnoise", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pnoise._get_version", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "pnoise.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pnoise.Noise", "xref": {"fqname": "pnoise.pnoise.Noise", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pnoise.pnoise", "documentation": ["pnoise library"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pnoise.pnoise.PERLIN_YWRAPB", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pnoise.pnoise.PERLIN_YWRAP", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pnoise.pnoise.PERLIN_ZWRAPB", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pnoise.pnoise.PERLIN_ZWRAP", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pnoise.pnoise.PERLIN_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "pnoise.pnoise.Noise", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pnoise.pnoise.Noise.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pnoise.pnoise.Noise.seed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "seed", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pnoise.pnoise.Noise.perlin", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Number", "xref": {"fqname": "numbers.Number", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Sequence", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Sequence", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Number", "xref": {"fqname": "numbers.Number", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Number", "xref": {"fqname": "numbers.Number", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Sequence", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Sequence", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Number", "xref": {"fqname": "numbers.Number", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "z", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Number", "xref": {"fqname": "numbers.Number", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Sequence", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Sequence", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Number", "xref": {"fqname": "numbers.Number", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "grid_mode", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Compute perlin noise for a range of values.\n\nEach of the x, y, and z argument may be 1D sequence of float. Perlin noise will be\ncomputed for each combination of each of the input argument and returns them in a\nNumpy array of shape (len(x), len(y), len(z)). If any of the input are scalar, they are\ninterpreted as a length-1 array.", "noinspection DuplicatedCode"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}]}